Sure! To write an if/then statement in C programming language, you can use the following syntax:

```
if (condition) {
  // code to execute if the condition is true
} else {
  // code to execute if the condition is false
}
```

For example, you can write an if/then statement to check if a number is positive, negative, or zero:

```
int num = 5;
if (num > 0) {
  printf("The number is positive.");
} else if (num < 0) {
  printf("The number is negative.");
} else {
  printf("The number is zero.");
}
```

This will print "The number is positive." on the console.
